From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude.ai.2026@simonlaux.de>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 17:30:03 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 62/62] web-app: recorder rows fit narrow (phone-sized)
 viewports
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

At 390px the recording row clipped Cancel/OK off-screen and the preview
row overflowed hard enough to shove the whole chat view sideways. Under
500px the recorder now wraps (preview controls take the full first line,
buttons the second) and the desktop-sized cancel/finish margins shrink.
Also fixes the <=400px live-waveform hide, which was silently overridden
by the base rule declared later in the file (same specificity, later
source order wins) — the compound selector now out-ranks it, matching the
volumeBar pattern next to it.

Verified with MOBILE=1 scripts/shot-voice-player.mjs (390x844, touch).
---
 .../AudioRecorder/styles.module.scss          | 26 ++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/packages/frontend/src/components/AudioRecorder/styles.module.scss b/packages/frontend/src/components/AudioRecorder/styles.module.scss
index 1c4cc49fc..889241758 100644
--- a/packages/frontend/src/components/AudioRecorder/styles.module.scss
+++ b/packages/frontend/src/components/AudioRecorder/styles.module.scss
@@ -167,7 +167,9 @@
       display: none;
     }
   }
-  .liveWaveform {
+  // Compound selector: the base .liveWaveform rule is declared later in this
+  // file and would win a same-specificity tie, un-hiding the waveform.
+  .liveWaveformContainer .liveWaveform {
     display: none;
   }
 }
@@ -353,3 +355,25 @@
   display: flex;
   align-items: center;
 }
+
+// Narrow viewports (phone-sized): the recording row (pause+mic+timer+meter+
+// picker+pill+cancel+ok) and the preview row (player + three buttons) don't
+// fit on one 390px line — let them wrap and drop the desktop-sized margins.
+// ponytail: one breakpoint, tuned against `MOBILE=1 scripts/shot-voice-player.mjs`.
+@media (max-width: 500px) {
+  .audioRecorder {
+    flex-wrap: wrap;
+  }
+  .previewControls {
+    flex-basis: 100%;
+  }
+  .cancel,
+  .stopRecording {
+    margin-inline-start: 6px;
+  }
+  // Doubled class to out-rank the base block's nested `&.stopRecording`
+  // (margin-inline-end: 40px) at equal position-independent specificity.
+  .stopRecording.stopRecording {
+    margin-inline-end: 6px;
+  }
+}
